name: Rumah Jennes
address: Jl. Jennes No.8, Buduk, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1: Great place, cozy and quiet, the house looks great there's a lot of charm and style to it, there's also 2 cute dogs one of which made me laugh, it would just stand there, right in front of you not moving waiting to be petted, not begging no tail wagging ..nothing, like he knew it would eventually happen ü§î
review 2: Home away from home! Whenever I come to Bali I will always stay here, the hosts are so friendly and helpful, the bed is comfy, the AC is cold and the shower is warm. So many beautiful little details that make you feel at home. There is a communal kitchen available for cooking or making tea/coffee and a fridge and beautiful green garden to sit and read or snuggle with the 2 dogs Baileys and Zena. The beach, amazing food and coffee and the hustle and bustle of canggu  is about a 10 min scooter ride away and the hosts are always happy to arrange a rental for you. You won‚Äôt regret staying at Rumah Jennes Guesthouse!
review 3: Our month long stay at Rumah Jennes was totally incredible. The location is perfectly situated away from the craziness of Canggu (15 min scooter to beach), Pritha, Lupo and their wonderful staff became our friends, and the dogs provided great security and cuddles. This is the only place we want to stay in Canggu, and hope to come back soon! Much appreciation for providing everything we could have asked for from an accommodation- and making us feel so at home.
review 4: Omg, such a beautifull place in piecefull local village, still close to beaches and canggu by bike. Friendly hosts, super clean and comfortable rooms, beautifull details, furniture, even swing in the kitchen! Can not wait till i will be back to Bali, i will deffinetly stay there, because i feel there just like at home‚ù§Ô∏è
review 5: Everytime come back to this nice place when i am a few days in canggu area. The hosts and the staff  there are super friendly and will help you with everything.
